quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  18,60,"Recall how Moses said to his servant, \"I shall not give up until I reach the place where both seas meet, even if it takes me years"
  18,61,"But when at last they came to the land where the two seas met, they forgot their fish and it swiftly made its way into the sea"
  18,62,"After they had passed the place, Moses said to his young companion, \"Bring us our morning meal; we have indeed been fatigued by this journey"
  18,63,"He replied, \"Did you see when we were resting by the rock, that I forgot the fish? Satan made me forget it, so I did not mention it. It made its way to the sea in a miraculous way"
  18,64,"Moses said, \"That is just what we were looking for.\" So they went back the way they had come"
  18,65,and they found one of Our servants to whom We had granted Our mercy and had given a knowledge from Ourself
  18,66,"Moses said to him, \"May I follow you, so that you may guide me by what you have been taught"
  18,67,"He replied, \"You will not be able to bear with me patiently"
  18,68,How could you be patient in matters beyond your knowledge
  18,69,"Moses said, \"God willing, you will find me patient, and I will not disobey you in any thing"
  18,70,"He said, \"Well then, if you would follow me, do not ask me about anything till I speak of it to you"